'''James Thomas Jr.''' (born April 22, 1951 in {{city-state|Macon|Georgia}}) is a former [[American football]] [[cornerback]] in the [[National Football League]]. He was drafted by the [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] 24th overall in the [[1973 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at [[Florida State Seminoles football|Florida State]].

Thomas also played for the [[Denver Broncos]].

